1
00:00:19,786 --> 00:00:22,084
A couple pretzels, please.

2
00:00:22,655 --> 00:00:25,123
What the heck, make it a dozen.

3
00:00:25,291 --> 00:00:27,020
I need my salt.

4
00:00:29,229 --> 00:00:31,254
- Taxi! Taxi!
- Thank you.

5
00:00:31,464 --> 00:00:33,227
What the...?

6
00:00:34,034 --> 00:00:35,968
Taxi! Taxi!

7
00:00:36,169 --> 00:00:39,332
- Here, let me help you.
- I've got it.

8
00:00:39,506 --> 00:00:42,441
No, I don't want you to think
everyone in Central City's a jerk!

9
00:00:43,243 --> 00:00:44,471
Thanks.

10
00:00:45,111 --> 00:00:47,477
- Hey, listen, you okay?
- I'm fine.

11
00:00:47,647 --> 00:00:50,616
Well, I'm from the neighborhood
if you're lost or anything.

12
00:00:51,684 --> 00:00:52,878
Are those pretzels?

13
00:00:54,054 --> 00:00:57,615
Yeah. Yeah. Help yourself.

14
00:01:06,866 --> 00:01:09,334
Listen, stop me if I'm out of line here...

15
00:01:09,536 --> 00:01:12,334
...but when was the last time
you had something to eat?

16
00:01:12,572 --> 00:01:15,405
I gotta go. Thanks again.

17
00:01:15,742 --> 00:01:17,232
Sure.

18
00:01:35,028 --> 00:01:36,620
Hello, Stacy.

19
00:01:38,264 --> 00:01:40,994
Can we offer you a lift?

20
00:01:43,036 --> 00:01:44,435
Bodey!

21
00:01:44,938 --> 00:01:47,168
Hey! Hey!

22
00:01:52,545 --> 00:01:55,378
Somebody help me!

23
00:01:59,018 --> 00:02:00,144
Get away from me!

24
00:02:02,122 --> 00:02:04,613
Come on, Stacy, relax.
Give me the knapsack.

25
00:02:04,791 --> 00:02:07,589
Get away from me.
Why can't you just leave us alone?

26
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:08,920
Good question.

27
00:02:26,412 --> 00:02:27,936
Sorry.

28
00:02:28,114 --> 00:02:30,207
I guess dinner's on him.

29
00:02:35,688 --> 00:02:38,782
Are you okay, miss? I heard a scream.

30
00:02:38,958 --> 00:02:40,789
No. It's all right.

31
00:02:40,960 --> 00:02:44,657
- I thought I saw someone chasing you.
- They...

32
00:02:44,831 --> 00:02:46,799
They just wanted my stuff.

33
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:50,663
No offense, but I saw
what was in your suitcase.

34
00:02:51,504 --> 00:02:53,631
It's hardly worth stealing.

35
00:02:54,340 --> 00:02:56,399
Wait. Wait.

36
00:02:58,144 --> 00:03:00,669
I'm a cop, all right?

37
00:03:01,714 --> 00:03:03,944
Please, let me help you.

38
00:03:06,085 --> 00:03:10,818
I would be happy if you could just get us
to a street mission or something.

39
00:03:10,990 --> 00:03:13,515
I am dead broke...

40
00:03:13,726 --> 00:03:16,126
...and we could really use...

41
00:03:16,329 --> 00:03:19,298
...a bed and a hot meal.
- We?

42
00:04:36,142 --> 00:04:38,576
Oh, my goodness,
don't you look beautiful.

43
00:04:38,745 --> 00:04:41,680
What did you tell the landlady
when you borrowed the highchair?

44
00:04:41,848 --> 00:04:43,873
You're now my cousin from Seattle.

45
00:04:44,083 --> 00:04:46,142
- Did she buy that?
- I hope so.

46
00:04:46,352 --> 00:04:50,311
I'm telling you, in this building,
gossip is a major-league sport.

47
00:04:51,057 --> 00:04:53,787
Let me do that. You go ahead and eat.
You must be starved.

48
00:04:54,027 --> 00:04:55,619
- Are you sure...?
- Yeah, no problem.

49
00:04:55,795 --> 00:04:58,127
My brother used to bring his kid
into the station.

50
00:04:58,298 --> 00:05:00,391
We'd take turns taking care of him.

51
00:05:00,566 --> 00:05:02,534
He used to take his naps...

52
00:05:02,735 --> 00:05:04,862
...in a desk drawer.
What do you think of that?

53
00:05:05,038 --> 00:05:09,407
Here it comes. Now open that mouth.
Yes. Yes.

54
00:05:12,145 --> 00:05:15,273
Here you go. All right.
Now some for me.

55
00:05:16,316 --> 00:05:17,715
Good.

56
00:05:19,986 --> 00:05:22,580
What? Am I doing this okay?

57
00:05:23,323 --> 00:05:27,657
Better than okay. I'm usually
the only one she lets feed her.

58
00:05:29,429 --> 00:05:31,522
I think she's got a crush on you, Barry.

59
00:05:31,698 --> 00:05:33,859
The feeling is mutual.

60
00:05:35,668 --> 00:05:37,693
There. All right.

61
00:05:38,171 --> 00:05:39,604
Okay.

62
00:05:40,239 --> 00:05:41,365
Stacy...

63
00:05:42,442 --> 00:05:44,637
...what kind of trouble you in?

64
00:05:46,079 --> 00:05:47,307
What do you mean?

65
00:05:47,847 --> 00:05:49,371
Well, back there on the street...

66
00:05:49,549 --> 00:05:52,677
...it seemed like you kept
looking over your shoulder.

67
00:05:53,319 --> 00:05:55,480
Like you thought somebody
was watching you.

68
00:05:55,688 --> 00:05:57,713
Just habit, I guess.

69
00:05:58,157 --> 00:06:00,853
Lily and I have been on the road
a while.

70
00:06:04,330 --> 00:06:05,797
Barry?

71
00:06:06,332 --> 00:06:08,766
- I think Lily's finished.
- What?

72
00:06:09,669 --> 00:06:11,830
Yeah, I think she is.

73
00:06:13,172 --> 00:06:14,537
Come here.

74
00:06:16,142 --> 00:06:19,578
What a mess. What a mess.

75
00:06:19,979 --> 00:06:23,506
Sure it's all right, us staying here?
I mean, you've already done a lot.

76
00:06:23,683 --> 00:06:26,880
What, a little Chinese takeout?
That's no big deal.

77
00:06:27,220 --> 00:06:29,984
Besides, in the morning I'll take you
to a place downtown...

78
00:06:30,156 --> 00:06:32,647
...where you and Lily can stay...

79
00:06:32,825 --> 00:06:34,520
...until you figure things out.

80
00:06:34,861 --> 00:06:36,260
I don't know, Barry.

81
00:06:36,462 --> 00:06:39,431
We're only gonna be in Central City
a couple of days.

82
00:06:40,199 --> 00:06:42,565
Well, think it over, that's all.

83
00:06:42,969 --> 00:06:44,732
Oh, yeah.

84
00:06:44,904 --> 00:06:48,305
Listen, when you're ready,
you can take my room upstairs, okay?

85
00:06:48,508 --> 00:06:51,807
- I'll bunk down here with Earl.
- Thanks.

86
00:06:52,545 --> 00:06:56,037
Can you look after her for a couple
of minutes? I'm gonna go wash up.

87
00:06:56,215 --> 00:06:58,342
Yeah, I think I can manage.

88
00:06:58,684 --> 00:07:00,652
Here we go.

89
00:07:04,424 --> 00:07:06,415
Hey, what's the matter, Earl?

90
00:07:06,592 --> 00:07:10,688
Don't worry, you haven't been replaced.
Besides, you'd love having a baby around.

91
00:07:12,031 --> 00:07:15,091
Okay. Here we are.

92
00:07:16,035 --> 00:07:18,026
Better give me this.

93
00:07:19,672 --> 00:07:21,037
Toy.

94
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:22,707
We need a baby toy here.

95
00:07:25,478 --> 00:07:30,211
Oh, thanks, Earl,
but pre-chewed is not the idea.

96
00:07:32,819 --> 00:07:36,050
It's a modern world, kid.
Get to know your tools.

97
00:07:36,589 --> 00:07:37,817
Watch.

98
00:07:40,059 --> 00:07:43,222
Very good.
You've played this game before.

99
00:07:44,730 --> 00:07:48,257
Well, just give it a try for a few days.
It's really a good setup here.

100
00:07:48,434 --> 00:07:50,197
Yeah, but I know
how these places work.

101
00:07:50,369 --> 00:07:52,701
There's probably a waiting list
a mile long.

102
00:07:52,872 --> 00:07:55,864
Don't worry about it. I got connections.

103
00:07:57,977 --> 00:07:59,911
- Hi.
- What's the matter?

104
00:08:00,079 --> 00:08:01,842
You too big to hug your mother?

105
00:08:02,014 --> 00:08:04,380
No way. Come over here.

106
00:08:04,617 --> 00:08:06,585
- How you doing?
- I'm fine.

107
00:08:07,620 --> 00:08:09,212
Come on in.

108
00:08:09,589 --> 00:08:11,181
You must be Stacy.

109
00:08:11,390 --> 00:08:14,655
And this is Lily. I'm Nora Allen.

110
00:08:14,861 --> 00:08:16,522
- You run this place?
- No.

111
00:08:16,696 --> 00:08:18,857
Voluntary duty, three days a week.

112
00:08:19,031 --> 00:08:23,058
Any more than that and his father
would turn our house into a poker parlor.

113
00:08:23,269 --> 00:08:26,261
Come on, let's take the grand tour.

114
00:08:26,472 --> 00:08:30,738
The bedrooms are upstairs.
Each mother and child shares one.

115
00:08:30,910 --> 00:08:33,435
Hi, Annie. And the kitchen is in here.

116
00:08:33,613 --> 00:08:37,777
Everybody helps out,
so be prepared to pitch in.

117
00:08:37,950 --> 00:08:41,681
And this is the dining room.
We also have classes in here.

118
00:08:41,888 --> 00:08:44,516
Childcare, self-defense.

119
00:08:44,891 --> 00:08:49,089
And this, Lily, is the playroom.

120
00:08:50,963 --> 00:08:53,488
Hi, Kathy. How's it going?

121
00:08:56,168 --> 00:08:57,635
So, what do you think, Stacy?

122
00:08:58,137 --> 00:08:59,570
It's wonderful.

123
00:09:00,540 --> 00:09:05,136
Why don't we go to my office and talk
about paperwork and all that dull stuff.

124
00:09:06,846 --> 00:09:08,871
Papers?

125
00:09:09,815 --> 00:09:12,909
I mean, if I stay,
it's confidential and everything?

126
00:09:13,152 --> 00:09:15,916
Oh, absolutely.
It's just for our records here.

127
00:09:16,389 --> 00:09:17,822
Okay?

128
00:09:18,324 --> 00:09:19,382
All right.

129
00:09:20,192 --> 00:09:22,820
Kathy, I need you to go to the market.

130
00:09:22,995 --> 00:09:24,860
Barry, will you watch the kids?

131
00:09:25,031 --> 00:09:27,795
What? Me? All of them? I can't do that.

132
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:31,595
Of course you can.
We'll only be a few minutes.

133
00:09:35,374 --> 00:09:36,773
Hi.

134
00:09:37,543 --> 00:09:39,135
Say hello to Uncle Barry.

135
00:09:50,222 --> 00:09:51,883
Here you go.

136
00:10:18,250 --> 00:10:19,478
Hungry?

137
00:10:19,652 --> 00:10:21,244
Yeah.

138
00:10:29,729 --> 00:10:33,096
Biscuits? Teething biscuits, huh?

139
00:10:33,265 --> 00:10:35,995
Barry, what's all that crying in here?

140
00:10:36,268 --> 00:10:39,294
Crying? Who's crying?

141
00:10:40,506 --> 00:10:42,804
Barry, why are you eating
teething biscuits?

142
00:10:43,609 --> 00:10:47,170
Oh, I got this molar. It's killing me.

143
00:10:50,850 --> 00:10:52,875
Yeah, I agree.

144
00:10:59,525 --> 00:11:02,289
And absolutely no disturbances
after 11 p.m.

145
00:11:02,461 --> 00:11:05,953
If he doesn't get precisely
seven hours of sleep, heads will roll.

146
00:11:06,132 --> 00:11:09,568
Also, we'll need new linens each day.
And I mean new.

147
00:11:09,769 --> 00:11:11,896
Buy them at Caruso's,
put them on the tab.

148
00:11:12,104 --> 00:11:14,902
He'll want fresh fish for supper.
Make sure that it's fresh.

149
00:11:15,107 --> 00:11:19,407
If it wasn't sucking seawater an hour ago,
he'll send it back. Got that?

150
00:11:20,012 --> 00:11:21,411
Fine.

151
00:11:24,016 --> 00:11:27,281
Three, two, one.

152
00:11:28,854 --> 00:11:32,551
The Flash? The Flash interceded?

153
00:11:32,725 --> 00:11:33,987
Yes, Mr. Moses.

154
00:11:34,160 --> 00:11:36,856
- And he took the child?
- Actually, we didn't see.

155
00:11:37,863 --> 00:11:41,424
That is, we're not sure whether
Stacy actually had Lily...

156
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:43,625
Lillian with her.

157
00:11:43,836 --> 00:11:46,771
- And where is Stacy now, Roy?
- We're working on that, sir.

158
00:11:47,006 --> 00:11:49,600
She's out of precise range.
But she hasn't left the city.

159
00:11:49,775 --> 00:11:52,005
The overall field reading
on the homing device...

160
00:11:52,178 --> 00:11:54,578
...is in the southwest sector.

161
00:11:56,716 --> 00:11:58,240
This ionizer won't be sufficient.

162
00:11:58,417 --> 00:12:00,942
- Get half a dozen more. And clear this.
- Yes, sir.

163
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:05,386
Central City. I was here 10 years ago.

164
00:12:05,624 --> 00:12:10,926
It's dirtier than I remember.
Even the air smells decayed.

165
00:12:11,564 --> 00:12:13,623
Do we have any friends here?

166
00:12:13,799 --> 00:12:16,734
Yes, sir. In the police department.
He's already been contacted.

167
00:12:16,902 --> 00:12:18,233
He's keeping his eyes open.

168
00:12:18,637 --> 00:12:21,731
Good. Now, what about this Flash?

169
00:12:21,907 --> 00:12:23,534
There must be a file on him.

170
00:12:23,709 --> 00:12:26,610
Sightings, rumors, et cetera. Get it.

171
00:12:29,415 --> 00:12:32,509
- You saw him?
- Yes, Mr. Moses.

172
00:12:32,718 --> 00:12:34,549
Big guy, red suit.

173
00:12:35,387 --> 00:12:37,787
Thank you. Very informative.

174
00:12:40,693 --> 00:12:42,456
What makes him tick?

175
00:12:42,628 --> 00:12:44,528
Genetic engineering?

176
00:12:44,864 --> 00:12:47,697
Or perhaps he's completely synthetic.

177
00:12:48,400 --> 00:12:51,767
Whatever he is, I have to find
a way to deal with him...

178
00:12:51,971 --> 00:12:54,201
...if he intervenes again.

179
00:12:55,007 --> 00:12:56,565
Interesting.

180
00:12:58,043 --> 00:13:01,410
I want Stacy found tonight.

181
00:13:02,181 --> 00:13:04,240
- Understood?
- No problem, Mr. Moses.

182
00:13:04,416 --> 00:13:08,113
Now, have them send up
a bowl of raw vegetables.

183
00:13:08,287 --> 00:13:10,949
And if they haven't been sterilized...

184
00:13:11,123 --> 00:13:12,715
...you will be.

185
00:13:14,426 --> 00:13:16,360
I'm sorry, I have to stick by the rules.

186
00:13:16,562 --> 00:13:20,259
No visitors after 5 p.m.
Except with prior consent.

187
00:13:20,432 --> 00:13:22,525
All right? Now, if you'll excuse me.

188
00:13:22,735 --> 00:13:25,499
But Stacy and Lillian are here,
aren't they?

189
00:13:25,671 --> 00:13:27,161
I really can't help you.

190
00:13:27,339 --> 00:13:31,298
Mrs. Allen, you were a young girl once.

191
00:13:31,477 --> 00:13:33,445
I'm sure you've had your share...

192
00:13:33,612 --> 00:13:37,309
...of lovers' quarrels
and misunderstandings.

193
00:13:37,483 --> 00:13:40,281
I mean, what kind of life is this?

194
00:13:40,452 --> 00:13:44,855
Alone on the streets with our baby.

195
00:13:46,559 --> 00:13:48,424
Stacy left a good home.

196
00:13:48,627 --> 00:13:51,528
She had everything
she could have desired.

197
00:13:51,697 --> 00:13:53,028
And I love her.

198
00:13:53,599 --> 00:13:55,123
I just want to get her back...

199
00:13:55,301 --> 00:13:58,202
...solve our differences,
take care of Lillian properly.

200
00:13:58,370 --> 00:13:59,769
Please...

201
00:14:00,105 --> 00:14:03,370
...can't I just speak to her now,
here, in the lobby, with you present?

202
00:14:03,542 --> 00:14:05,066
I'm afraid that's not possible.

203
00:14:05,377 --> 00:14:08,608
- I'm going to have to insist that you...
- Mrs. Allen.

204
00:14:09,481 --> 00:14:11,972
My husband is coming to pick me up
in a few minutes.

205
00:14:13,719 --> 00:14:16,085
My husband, the ex-policeman.

206
00:14:17,323 --> 00:14:18,984
I understand.

207
00:14:21,560 --> 00:14:24,654
I'm sorry to have bothered you.

208
00:14:38,344 --> 00:14:41,780
She's on the move. But she's close.
The signal's getting stronger.

209
00:14:42,681 --> 00:14:44,444
Just find her, Roy.

210
00:14:44,917 --> 00:14:47,909
I've got it. Bodey, turn right here.

211
00:14:57,429 --> 00:14:58,953
Stacy.

212
00:14:59,265 --> 00:15:01,290
I said I'd find you.

213
00:15:03,636 --> 00:15:07,402
It was such a useless exercise
on your part.

214
00:15:08,540 --> 00:15:10,269
And I was not happy...

215
00:15:10,476 --> 00:15:13,912
...that you exposed Lillian
to the perils of the road.

216
00:15:14,079 --> 00:15:15,706
Give me the baby.

217
00:15:19,852 --> 00:15:21,820
She's safe, Philip. You'll never find her.

218
00:15:21,987 --> 00:15:23,750
Never?

219
00:15:24,490 --> 00:15:26,287
You know me better.

220
00:15:27,726 --> 00:15:29,250
Put her in the car.

221
00:15:31,964 --> 00:15:33,932
I know how people
are about loaning things.

222
00:15:34,099 --> 00:15:36,499
I've got loads of LaserDiscs.
Take what you want.

223
00:15:36,669 --> 00:15:40,366
Great, because I have two nights off.
I wanna sit on my couch and watch movies.

224
00:15:40,539 --> 00:15:42,006
Okay. I have all the classics.

225
00:15:42,174 --> 00:15:44,005
<i>The Great Escape</i>,
<i>The Guns of Navarone.</i>

226
00:15:44,176 --> 00:15:46,576
God, Barry, don't you have any
with women in them?

227
00:15:46,745 --> 00:15:50,442
<i>Bullitt. Bullitt.</i>
Yeah, that has a woman. I think.

228
00:15:50,916 --> 00:15:52,508
How about <i>3 Godfathers</i>?

229
00:15:52,718 --> 00:15:57,246
Yeah, that's great. It's about these
three cowboys who find a baby.

230
00:16:00,626 --> 00:16:02,253
Oh, boy.

231
00:16:08,100 --> 00:16:09,328
Lily?

232
00:16:09,501 --> 00:16:12,732
One of your adventures before
you became the Flash, eh, Barry?

233
00:16:12,905 --> 00:16:16,568
Lily is Stacy's baby. Why on earth
would she leave her with me?

234
00:16:16,809 --> 00:16:20,301
"Dearest Barry, be back in the morning.
Please take care of Lily. Love..."

235
00:16:20,512 --> 00:16:23,481
A rather annoying cute little drawing
of a heart, "Stacy."

236
00:16:23,649 --> 00:16:27,016
- Are you sure you're not the father?
- Tina, this is no time for comedy.

237
00:16:27,252 --> 00:16:30,983
- What am I gonna do?
- Well, nothing out here.

238
00:16:31,824 --> 00:16:33,724
Take her inside here.

239
00:16:34,960 --> 00:16:37,588
Very quietly. Quietly. It's a baby.

240
00:16:38,163 --> 00:16:41,030
I can't believe this girl would leave
a baby with someone.

241
00:16:41,233 --> 00:16:43,394
Well, she's been running away
from something.

242
00:16:43,569 --> 00:16:45,867
She's obviously very confused.

243
00:16:46,071 --> 00:16:49,871
- But she barely knows...
- No, Tina! You'll wake the baby.

244
00:16:50,876 --> 00:16:52,673
Carefully, carefully.

245
00:16:52,845 --> 00:16:55,006
Okay. There.

246
00:16:57,916 --> 00:17:02,148
Besides, it's only for one night.
How difficult could it be?

247
00:17:05,290 --> 00:17:08,487
- Okay. All right. Now, don't panic.
- Okay.

248
00:17:08,660 --> 00:17:10,287
Just rock. Rock. Gently.

249
00:17:10,929 --> 00:17:12,419
Gently. Gently.

250
00:17:12,598 --> 00:17:14,065
- Pick her up.
