00:34:14,252 --> 00:34:15,879
Now, Stacy...

490
00:34:16,054 --> 00:34:18,079
...I think it's time.

491
00:34:18,289 --> 00:34:20,314
The whole story.

492
00:34:23,261 --> 00:34:26,628
And after you got pregnant, you found out
about Philip's criminal record.

493
00:34:27,131 --> 00:34:30,498
That's when Philip told me
he never really loved me.

494
00:34:30,668 --> 00:34:32,727
That he had used me...

495
00:34:33,971 --> 00:34:36,735
...because I was the perfect mother
for his child.

496
00:34:38,076 --> 00:34:39,566
I just talked to the feds.

497
00:34:40,812 --> 00:34:42,609
They'll assist.

498
00:34:43,281 --> 00:34:46,682
They've been trying to nail Moses
to the wall for years.

499
00:34:47,018 --> 00:34:48,315
You'll never catch him.

500
00:34:48,986 --> 00:34:51,113
He's not giving up until
he gets what he wants.

501
00:34:51,289 --> 00:34:53,655
But if we could set a trap...

502
00:34:57,361 --> 00:35:00,228
No! I will not risk my baby!

503
00:35:00,398 --> 00:35:03,128
Listen, you wanna put a stop
to this guy, or what?

504
00:35:03,301 --> 00:35:06,031
I will not let Lily be used as bait!

505
00:35:06,237 --> 00:35:09,035
- I'm sorry.
- Don't apologize.

506
00:35:09,207 --> 00:35:12,108
Now, it's your decision.
For you and for Lily.

507
00:35:12,276 --> 00:35:15,336
Sooner or later you're gonna have to
face this problem head-on.

508
00:35:15,513 --> 00:35:19,711
- You can't keep running away.
- I'm so confused!

509
00:35:21,486 --> 00:35:24,046
Maybe Philip was right.
Maybe I am an unfit mother.

510
00:35:24,222 --> 00:35:26,053
Now, you listen to me.

511
00:35:26,624 --> 00:35:31,391
You are a tough girl, Stacy. A smart girl.
I don't care what Moses says.

512
00:35:32,163 --> 00:35:34,996
Now, your love for Lily
will get you through this...

513
00:35:35,166 --> 00:35:37,191
...whatever you decide.

514
00:35:40,538 --> 00:35:41,732
All right.

515
00:35:44,175 --> 00:35:47,372
Lieutenant Garfield,
I'll help you catch Philip.

516
00:35:48,513 --> 00:35:51,949
We must leave Central City.
But not without my daughter.

517
00:35:52,116 --> 00:35:55,313
She's the link to my future. My heiress.

518
00:35:55,486 --> 00:35:59,718
Listen, they just took the girl
over to the home right now.

519
00:36:01,726 --> 00:36:04,024
But there's something
you ought to know about.

520
00:36:07,431 --> 00:36:08,659
I see.

521
00:36:08,833 --> 00:36:11,597
That calls for an appropriate
countermeasure then.

522
00:36:15,239 --> 00:36:19,369
<i>Lieutenant, do you want us to use</i>
<i>procedure code alpha? Over.</i>

523
00:36:19,544 --> 00:36:23,742
That's right. I want this done
without the usual fuss.

524
00:36:23,915 --> 00:36:27,214
- Everything's under control.
- Yeah, except my girdle's killing me.

525
00:36:27,385 --> 00:36:30,877
- What, you think you're the only one?
- Hey, guys, knock it off, all right?

526
00:36:31,322 --> 00:36:33,449
We don't wanna wake Lillian.

527
00:36:35,426 --> 00:36:37,087
- <i>Lieutenant.</i>
- Just a minute.

528
00:36:46,404 --> 00:36:49,100
- Heads up.
- All set.

529
00:37:03,120 --> 00:37:07,454
Good evening, ma'am. Evening, ladies.
The main office sent me down.

530
00:37:07,625 --> 00:37:10,617
There seems to be some kind
of power outage in one of your tran...

531
00:37:10,795 --> 00:37:12,387
Oh, look at the baby.

532
00:37:12,730 --> 00:37:14,459
- All right, ladies...
- Freeze, punk.

533
00:37:15,800 --> 00:37:18,098
- Roy.
- I can't believe it.

534
00:37:18,302 --> 00:37:21,135
- He set me up.
- Moses.

535
00:37:21,672 --> 00:37:24,573
Oh, my God. What about Lily?

536
00:37:24,775 --> 00:37:26,538
Barry?

537
00:37:26,844 --> 00:37:28,539
Barry?!

538
00:37:34,185 --> 00:37:37,848
I cleared the back entrance for you.
But there's one uniform on watch upstairs.

539
00:37:38,022 --> 00:37:40,354
We'll deal with him, Mills. Thank you.

540
00:37:44,428 --> 00:37:47,090
Yes. Just in case.

541
00:37:47,498 --> 00:37:49,090
Let's go.

542
00:37:51,535 --> 00:37:54,527
So are you and Sabrina
getting serious?

543
00:37:54,739 --> 00:37:57,264
- Well, I guess.
- Can I help you, gentlemen?

544
00:37:57,475 --> 00:37:59,966
Julio, it's the man
who came to the home!

545
00:38:03,281 --> 00:38:04,771
Bodey.

546
00:38:06,117 --> 00:38:09,917
- You're not going to take that child!
- Oh, really?

547
00:38:10,655 --> 00:38:13,055
That's one woman
I wouldn't threaten, Moses!

548
00:38:13,224 --> 00:38:16,125
I'm ready for you this time,
you speed freak.

549
00:38:19,397 --> 00:38:22,525
This ultrasonic weapon is doing things
to your equilibrium...

550
00:38:22,700 --> 00:38:25,863
...that shouldn't happen to a dog.

551
00:39:06,744 --> 00:39:08,473
Thank you very much.

552
00:39:10,281 --> 00:39:12,749
- Where you been?
- I've been checking with the station.

553
00:39:12,917 --> 00:39:14,282
Mom and Julio are all right.

554
00:39:14,452 --> 00:39:17,319
They just have headaches
the size of Mt. Rushmore.

555
00:39:17,788 --> 00:39:20,154
- You okay?
- Yeah.

556
00:39:20,891 --> 00:39:23,689
According to the FBI,
Moses spent the past few weeks...

557
00:39:23,861 --> 00:39:27,763
...liquidating all his financial holdings
and transferring them into bearer bonds.

558
00:39:27,932 --> 00:39:32,460
They figure he's got close
to 10 million in assets.

559
00:39:32,903 --> 00:39:36,771
And look at this, huh?
All the exits to the city are covered.

560
00:39:37,007 --> 00:39:40,443
- Highways, trains, the airport...
- Don't bet on it.

561
00:39:40,611 --> 00:39:43,375
Moses is too smart to let himself
get backed into a corner.

562
00:39:43,547 --> 00:39:44,775
He's got an escape route.

563
00:39:44,949 --> 00:39:48,407
What I can't figure is how they knew
where the baby really was...

564
00:39:48,586 --> 00:39:51,783
...and how they got in and out
of police headquarters so easily.

565
00:39:51,956 --> 00:39:53,617
Maybe he had help.

566
00:39:53,824 --> 00:39:55,792
- Meaning what?
- Meaning a man like Moses...

567
00:39:55,960 --> 00:39:59,054
...can buy almost anything.
Or anybody.

568
00:39:59,230 --> 00:40:00,697
I don't like your implication.

569
00:40:00,865 --> 00:40:03,766
Who was on duty
at the back entrance tonight?

570
00:40:08,205 --> 00:40:10,366
- <i>Central City Police.</i>
- This is Garfield.

571
00:40:10,541 --> 00:40:12,975
- Who was on the back door tonight?
- <i>Dave Mills, sir.</i>

572
00:40:13,144 --> 00:40:16,580
- Dave Mills? All right, I wanna talk to him.
- <i>He already left.</i>

573
00:40:16,814 --> 00:40:19,146
- He did?
- <i>Yes. He volunteered for roadblock duty.</i>

574
00:40:19,316 --> 00:40:21,580
- When?
- <i>About an hour ago.</i>

575
00:40:22,086 --> 00:40:23,417
Where?

576
00:40:28,359 --> 00:40:31,226
- He volunteered for roadblock duty.
- Where?

577
00:40:31,762 --> 00:40:33,161
Skyline Drive.

578
00:40:34,532 --> 00:40:36,693
That's the road to the old airport.

579
00:40:41,539 --> 00:40:45,532
This is Garfield. I want all available units
out to Skyline Drive now!

580
00:40:48,779 --> 00:40:51,213
Lillian. Lillian, look at this.

581
00:40:51,382 --> 00:40:54,715
You know what this is?
This is a bond. A bearer bond.

582
00:40:54,919 --> 00:40:58,980
And they are better than money
because you can take them anywhere.

583
00:40:59,156 --> 00:41:01,181
And they are all ours.

584
00:41:01,425 --> 00:41:05,054
All $ 10 million worth.

585
00:41:05,229 --> 00:41:08,892
Yes. That's right, $ 10 million.

586
00:41:09,533 --> 00:41:10,932
Roadblock up ahead.

587
00:41:17,708 --> 00:41:20,472
I just heard there's a half a dozen units
headed this way.

588
00:41:20,644 --> 00:41:22,236
They must know your escape route.

589
00:41:22,446 --> 00:41:25,438
But the time they get here,
we'll be long gone. Move your car.

590
00:41:25,616 --> 00:41:28,881
If they know about the airfield,
they know about me. You gotta take me.

591
00:41:29,053 --> 00:41:32,250
- I don't think so.
- You can't leave me here. I know too much.

592
00:41:32,623 --> 00:41:35,683
You know, I do believe
you're right about that.

593
00:41:39,897 --> 00:41:41,364
Hey!

594
00:41:51,342 --> 00:41:53,742
Okay, here we go. Come on.

595
00:41:58,382 --> 00:42:00,873
Bodey, do something with this,
will you?

596
00:42:01,051 --> 00:42:03,576
Get her to stop that racket.
It's giving me a headache.

597
00:42:03,754 --> 00:42:05,779
Mr. Moses, I think it's wet.

598
00:42:05,990 --> 00:42:08,049
Then change it.

599
00:42:08,292 --> 00:42:10,419
I'm loading the plane. Don't dally.

600
00:42:13,364 --> 00:42:15,491
Don't worry. Don't cry.

601
00:42:19,036 --> 00:42:21,664
Everything's gonna be all right.

602
00:42:23,507 --> 00:42:25,566
It will be as soon
as you're out of her life.

603
00:42:26,343 --> 00:42:30,609
Face it, Bodey, you're really not
the maternal type.

604
00:42:32,616 --> 00:42:35,107
I see you more as hard labor.

605
00:42:36,153 --> 00:42:39,919
In fact, I know of an opening
you'd be perfect for:

606
00:42:40,124 --> 00:42:43,321
Making license plates for the state
for the next 20 years.

607
00:42:45,396 --> 00:42:48,797
Personally, I think you'd look
a lot better in gray.

608
00:42:48,966 --> 00:42:50,228
Prison gray.

609
00:43:05,816 --> 00:43:07,340
Lily?

610
00:43:41,018 --> 00:43:43,111
You've broken
your last commandment, Moses.

611
00:43:43,320 --> 00:43:44,753
Give me the baby.

612
00:43:44,922 --> 00:43:48,323
She is my daughter. Mine!

613
00:43:52,696 --> 00:43:55,494
Oh, well. Easy come, easy go.

614
00:43:55,666 --> 00:43:57,463
No!

615
00:44:04,341 --> 00:44:05,899
No!

616
00:44:08,345 --> 00:44:11,280
No. No!

617
00:44:11,749 --> 00:44:13,614
No! Please!

618
00:44:24,728 --> 00:44:26,889
- All right, move in. Let's get them.
- Yes, sir.

619
00:44:27,064 --> 00:44:28,725
- Lily!
- Spread out around here.

620
00:44:30,000 --> 00:44:32,798
Has anybody seen my baby?

621
00:44:33,804 --> 00:44:35,271
Lily!

622
00:44:36,306 --> 00:44:37,705
Come on. Come on.

623
00:44:37,875 --> 00:44:39,206
Oh, my God.

624
00:44:39,376 --> 00:44:42,903
My baby! Has anybody seen my baby?

625
00:44:44,982 --> 00:44:46,415
Sweetie.

626
00:44:47,451 --> 00:44:49,043
Oh, sweetie.

627
00:44:55,592 --> 00:44:57,856
Did you miss me, honey?

628
00:45:05,703 --> 00:45:08,570
- How's Lily?
- I can hardly keep up with her.

629
00:45:08,739 --> 00:45:10,764
- Your mother's been wonderful.
- My mom?

630
00:45:10,974 --> 00:45:13,033
- That lady?
- Yeah, your mom.

631
00:45:13,243 --> 00:45:15,040
She got me a job downtown.

632
00:45:15,212 --> 00:45:18,181
I finally think that Lily and I
are gonna be all right.

633
00:45:19,016 --> 00:45:23,510
More than anyone else, it's because of you
that Lily and I are still together.

634
00:45:23,687 --> 00:45:27,680
Well, I guess the Flash
had something to do with it, huh?

635
00:45:28,892 --> 00:45:33,352
Listen, I just want you to know
that if you and Lily ever need anything...

636
00:45:33,530 --> 00:45:36,124
- Mama.
- She said your name.

637
00:45:36,333 --> 00:45:39,268
Yeah, she's just starting to talk.

638
00:45:39,470 --> 00:45:43,270
- Lily, look who's here.
- Hey, cute stuff. How you doing?

639
00:45:43,440 --> 00:45:45,908
- Uncle Barry.
- Flash.

640
00:45:46,710 --> 00:45:51,044
- You know, it sounded like she said...
- "Splash." She said, "Splash."

641
00:45:51,248 --> 00:45:53,011
You know, time for her bath, I think.

642
00:45:53,183 --> 00:45:56,175
- Is that what you want? To take a bath?
- I think that's it.

643
00:45:56,420 --> 00:45:57,887
Come on.

644
00:46:00,691 --> 00:46:02,852
- Bye, Barry.
- Bye.

645
00:46:03,026 --> 00:46:04,721
Flash.

646
00:46:07,097 --> 00:46:08,655
Flash.

647
00:46:10,667 --> 00:46:12,328
Kids.

648
00:47:21,271 --> 00:47:23,262
[ENGLISH]



